# Config for the Spacory Product / Engineer agents. dispatch.sh sources this
# file (exported) so every value here is inherited by the run-*.sh children and
# the headless Claude sessions they launch. This is the single place to configure
# an unattended agent run.
#
# SETUP: copy this file to ".agents/.env" (which is gitignored) and fill in real
# values. Never put real credentials in this template or in the *-agent-prompt.md
# files — those are committed to the repo.
#
#   cp .agents/.env.example .agents/.env
#
# In CI, do NOT use this file — inject the secrets as repository secrets instead.

# ── Telegram wrap-up notifications (notify.sh) ───────────────────────────────
# - TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: create a bot via @BotFather and paste the token it returns.
# - TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID:   message your bot, then read result[].message.chat.id from
#                       https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/getUpdates
# See .agents/README.md for the full walkthrough.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=

# ── Model & permissions (run-*.sh) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# CLAUDE_MODEL: model the headless agents run on. Unset → the CLI's session
# default. "opus" tracks the newest Opus; use an exact id (e.g. claude-opus-4-8)
# to lock a version.
CLAUDE_MODEL=opus

# CLAUDE_PERMISSION_MODE: default "acceptEdits". Use "bypassPermissions" for
# fully unattended runs where a needed command isn't allowlisted in
# .claude/settings.json (only in a trusted environment).
#CLAUDE_PERMISSION_MODE=acceptEdits

# ── Dispatch pipeline (dispatch.sh) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# SPACORY_MAX_ROUNDS: resolve↔review rounds before a PR is marked blocked
# (default 5). Counted since the linked issue's body was last edited.
#SPACORY_MAX_ROUNDS=5

# SPACORY_AUTOMERGE: "1" to squash-merge an accepted PR once CI is green.
# Default off — the agents never self-merge; this is a human opt-in.
#SPACORY_AUTOMERGE=0
